lead_paragraph: The internationally recognized Parliament voted down a proposed 32-member cabinet in a blow to international efforts to help form a unified government.

headline.main: Libyan Lawmakers Reject U.N.-Backed Unity Government
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Africa; Libya: Parliament Rejects Cabinet Plan

abstract: Libya's internationally recognized Parliament, which meets in Tobruk, rejects proposal for United Nations-backed 32-member unity cabinet, complicating efforts to reconcile country's factions.
